Here is the function `clean_column` that meets your requirements. It lowercases the column name, strips any leading or trailing whitespaces, and replaces any spaces or hyphens with an underscore:

```julia
function clean_column(col::AbstractString)
    # lowercase the string
    col = lowercase(col);

    # remove leading/trailing whitespaces
    col = strip(col);

    # replace spaces and hyphens with underscores
    col = replace(col, ' ', '_');
    col = replace(col, '-', '_');

    return col;
end
```
This function can be used as follows:

```julia
column_name = "My Column";
cleaned_column = clean_column(column_name);
println("Cleaned column name is : ", cleaned_column);  # Prints: "Cleaned column name is : my_column"
```
Please replace `"My Column"` with your actual column name.
